column2: Fully insured for retirement benefits, survivor benefits, or both

column15: SOURCE: Social Security Administration, Continuous Work History Sample, 1 percent sample.

NOTES: Insured workers are those who have accumulated sufficient quarters of coverage over their working lifetimes to be eligible for benefits.
          Figures are subject to revision.
Totals do not necessarily equal the sum of rounded components.
. . . = not applicable.
a. Figures exclude people at or above normal (or full) retirement age because they are not eligible to receive disability benefits.
